
1) What is the difference between the Thread and Runnable?
Thread is a class and Runnable is an interface

2) How do you start a thread using Runnable?

Create a class that implements Runnable and instantiate an object of type Thread. Then public void run()

3) How do you start a thread using Thread?

Create a class that extends Thread and call start()

4) How do you get a thread's name?

final String getName()

5) What does the "synchronize()" method do?

Controls when threads enter methods.

6) What does the "join()" method do?

The join method puts the current thread on wait until the thread on which itâ€™s called is dead.

7) What does the "sleep()" method do?

pause the execution of current thread for specified time in milliseconds

8) What is the one method you must write if you're implementing the Runnable class?

public void run()

9) Should you create that same method if you're extending Thread?

No

10) Why is multi-threading so cool?
Efficient. Allows a program to keep working on something while waiting for something else.

